Implementation details for P5.1 - State Reconciliation:

## Architecture
- Reconciler struct: wraps Store + AWS clients (EC2, ECS, ELBv2)
- findOrphanedResources: queries AWS for agent-deploy:* tagged resources
- findStaleEntries: checks local state references against AWS
- CleanupStaleEntries: marks stale entries as destroyed/stopped

## AWS Resource Discovery
- VPCs: DescribeVpcs with tag-key filter
- ECS Clusters: ListClusters + DescribeClusters with TAGS include
- ALBs: DescribeLoadBalancers + DescribeTags

## Detection Logic
1. Orphaned: AWS resource has agent-deploy:infra-id tag but no matching local entry
2. Stale: Local entry references VPC/ECS/ALB that doesn't exist in AWS

## CLI Integration
- -enable-reconcile: opt-in flag (default: false)
- -reconcile-region: AWS region to query (default: us-east-1)
- Runs once at startup, before MCP server begins accepting requests

## Error Handling
- Non-fatal: continues reconciliation even if some AWS queries fail
- Errors collected in ReconcileResult.Errors for reporting
- Each resource type checked independently

## Test Strategy
- Unit tests for data structures (ReconcileResult, OrphanedResource, StaleEntry)
- Store integration tests (create/list/update operations)
- Logic tests for counting and filtering (skip destroyed/stopped)
- No AWS mocking - tests focus on local state logic

## Why This Matters
Without reconciliation, operator has no visibility into:
- Forgotten AWS resources accruing costs
- Local state pointing to deleted resources
- Drift between local and cloud state
